headline: Investors Bet on Fewer Rate Cuts Following Solid Jobs Data
summary: Signs of a resilient labor market are causing investors to scale back bets on interest-rate cuts this year.  Interest-rate futures showed midday Thursday a roughly 37% chance that the Federal Reserve cuts interest rates just once or not at all this year, according to CME Group, up from 26% at the end of December.  The shift has led to an uptick in the yield on 2-year U.S. Treasury note, narrowing the gap between it and the 10-year U.S. Treasury yield.

headline: Chainlink, Cardano and Stellar Futures Begin Trading on CME Next Month
summary: CME Group plans to launch Cardano, Chainlink, and Stellar futures on February 9, pending approval.
